The paper deals with formal verification of multi-agent systems, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of temporal logic and strategy quantifiers suggests that the paper could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category. The focus on multi-agent systems and collaboration/antagonism between agents suggests that the paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Game Theory (cs.GT) categories. The use of incomplete observation and the preservation of decidability suggests that the paper could belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) category. Finally, the use of strategy contexts suggests that the paper could also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category.
